sentences: She was appointed Honorary Dame Commander of the Order of the British Empire on her 84th birthday in 1921.
On 10 November 1856, at age 19, she married a Russian count, Constantine de Guerbel.
In 1862, after Ward's last role in La Traviata, she retired due to vocal difficulties.
She published a volume of reminiscences, Before and Behind the Curtain in 1918.
Geneviève Ward, Countess de Guerbel, died of heart disease at her home in Hampstead on 18 August 1922, aged 85.

sentences: Lucy Geneviève Teresa Ward, Countess de Guerbel, DBE (27 March 1837 – 18 August 1922), also known as Countess de Guerbel and, sometimes, albeit inaccurately, as Dame Geneviève Ward, was a United Kingdom-based American-born Russian soprano and actress.
After a few years' stay in Europe, the family returned to New York, and soon afterward made the acquaintance of Henriette Sontag, who encouraged Ward to study singing.
